# Surya AI - Global Behavior Rules

## Core Principles
- **No Express.js**: Use native Node.js HTTP server only
- **Vanilla JavaScript**: No React, Vue, or heavy frameworks in core app
- **Modular Architecture**: Separate JS and CSS files, logical component organization
- **Security First**: All API keys server-side only, never exposed to client
- **Performance Focus**: Optimize for speed, minimal bundle size

## Code Style Rules
- **ES6+ Only**: Arrow functions, destructuring, template literals, async/await
- **Consistent Naming**: camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for classes
- **Error Handling**: Try/catch blocks for all async operations
- **Comments**: JSDoc for functions, inline comments for complex logic

## Architecture Constraints
- **Backend**: Native Node.js HTTP server with custom routing
- **Frontend**: Single-page application with vanilla JS
- **Storage**: JSON file-based (users.json, chats.json) - no databases yet
- **Authentication**: PBKDF2 password hashing, JWT-like bearer tokens
- **APIs**: Server-side proxy for all external services (InsForge, Google, etc.)

## Canvas IDE Rules
- **WebContainer Only**: No Blob URLs or iframe hacks
- **Vite + Tailwind**: Enforced tech stack for generated projects
- **Cross-Origin Isolation**: COOP + COEP headers required
- **Secure Context**: HTTPS or localhost only for SharedArrayBuffer

## Development Workflow
- **Testing**: Manual testing in browser, console logging for debugging
- **Version Control**: Git with feature branches, descriptive commit messages
- **Documentation**: Update docs on architecture changes
- **Security**: Never commit API keys or sensitive data

## File Organization
- **Root Level**: Core config files (CLAUDE.md, .clauderules, package.json)
- **frontend/**: HTML, CSS, JS modules (modular structure)
- **backend/**: Server-side logic and API handlers
- **data/**: JSON storage files (users, chats)
- **docs/**: Documentation and guides

## Quality Standards
- **Performance**: < 3 second load times, < 500KB bundle size
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance, keyboard navigation
- **Security**: OWASP top 10 compliance, input validation
- **Maintainability**: Modular code, clear separation of concerns

## AI Interaction Rules
- **Context Awareness**: Understand current project phase and architecture
- **Helpful Suggestions**: Provide actionable feedback and improvements
- **Code Quality**: Ensure generated code follows project standards
- **Documentation**: Update relevant docs when making architectural changes